"Iranian President: If sanctions against Iran are lifted, there is hope for a nuclear agreement to be reached - Xinhua News."
"Xinhua News, Tehran, December 11th (Reporters Gao Wencheng, Wang Shoubao): Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on the 11th in the Iranian capital of Tehran that if the United States lifts sanctions against Iran, comprehensive nuclear agreement talks can reach a "good agreement."
"According to news released on the website of the Iranian President, Rouhani said during a meeting with ambassadors from Iran's neighboring countries that by submitting proposals to the other parties related to the Iran nuclear deal, Iran has demonstrated its sincere intention to negotiate."
"If the US side makes a firm determination, the road to reaching an agreement will be smooth."
"The parties related to the Iran nuclear deal started talks in Vienna, Austria, the capital, in April of this year to discuss the issue of the restoration of compliance by the US and Iran."
"The new round of talks began in Vienna on November 29th and was temporarily suspended on December 3rd, to be continued on the 9th."